body:
The "fix" has not solved the problem. The problem is actually on how you write the validators into the genesis file. There is a difference between Parity and Nethermind. 

If you configure AuRa for Parity, the looks like this:
```
"engine": {
    "authorityRound": {
      "params": {
        "stepDuration": "30",
        "validators": {
          "list": [
            "0xAddress1",
            "0xAddress2",
            "0xAddress3"
          ]
        }
      }
    }
  }
```
For Nethermind it looks like that:
```
"engine": {
    "authorityRound": {
      "params": {
        "stepDuration": "30",
        "validators": {
          "multi": {
            "0": {
              "list": [
                "0xAddress1",
                "0xAddress2",
                "0xAddress3"
              ]
            }
          }
        }
      }
    }
  }
```
I actually realized the difference in one of your tutorials :)
Having one genesis file for Parity and one for Nethermind in that form and it works fine :)
